<p>

<b>Jacques Edward Vroom, Jr.</b> (born <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../040/16040.xml">
July 28</link>, <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../622/34622.xml">
1944</link>) is a retired expert in <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../239/665239.xml">
direct marketing</link>, narrator of the 2004 documentary Bush's Brain, and a world traveler who has accrued more than 36 million AAdvantage miles. He is perhaps best known for being half of <it>The Jack and Harry Show</it> duo in the late 1970's and early 1980's. The show appeared on KERA, the Dallas PBS station; combining 1950's music with clever banter between the two hostsâ€”and guests, most of whom were imaginary.</p>

